WTO Calls for vaccine manufacture locally. The Director General of the World Trade Organization, Dr Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala says Nigeria must begin to transit it's economy to remain afloat as well as improve its foreign trade policies to earn more foreign currency.  Dr Okonjo-Iweala who gave the advice at the Presidential Villa Abuja on Monday, shortly after a meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari to thank him and Nigerians for their support for her candidacy in WTO DG race, disclosed that her brief with Buhari centred on how Nigeria can work with the W.T.O. to improve its economy, boost and export the talents of young Nigerians as well as tap from the African Continental Free Trade Agreement.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the WTO DG also called for immediate efforts to address the nation's healthcare infrastructure to contain future pandemics, stressing that Nigeria should start looking at establishing the capacity for manufacturing vaccines locally.